description: The Supreme Court has halted a Jharkhand High Court order for a CBI investigation into an alleged assembly recruitment scam. The court admitted the assembly secretariat's plea challenging the order's legality. The High Court had mandated the probe due to alleged non-cooperation from the secretariat in addressing the alleged irregularities.
title: SC stays Jharkhand HC order for CBI probe into job scam in House

description: The Indian government has issued a directive mandating that eye banks collect a minimum of 100 corneas annually to retain their operating licenses. This decision, aimed at addressing the issue of underperforming eye banks, could impact the accessibility of corneal transplants for individuals with vision loss due to corneal damage.
title: Eye banks that don’t collect 100 corneas a year can lose licence

description: Tensions are rising as tribal groups demand the bodies of 10 Hmar individuals killed in Manipur be returned to their village through Mizoram.  Protesters allege delays in autopsies and reject claims of necessary DNA matching.  The groups insist on honoring the deceased as heroes in Mizoram before their final journey to Manipur, opposing any alternate routes.
title: Impasse over handing bodies of 10 slain Hmar ‘militants’ to kin

description: Former Jharkhand CM and BJP leader Babulal Marandi addressed key election issues, highlighting concerns over demographic changes impacting tribal communities and alleging corruption within the JMM-Congress alliance. Marandi emphasized BJP's commitment to protecting tribal rights and refuted accusations of polarisation tactics. He also expressed confidence in BJP's victory, downplaying personal ambitions for the CM position.
title: Interview: 'Corruption key issue, Jharkhand yearning for a change'

description: A record-breaking 5.6 lakh Indians migrated to OECD countries in 2022, a 35% surge, solidifying India's position as the top source of new migrants. The UK, US, and Canada remained popular destinations, although some nations signal potential tightening of immigration policies. Concurrently, Indian nationals acquiring OECD citizenship surged by 40%, reaching 1.
title: 5.6 lakh Indians migrated to rich OECD countries in 2022
Driver dies as truck falls off bridge amid dense fog

description: The Indian Council of Social Science Research (ICSSR) has announced expanded funding for social science research, with a budget of Rs 235 crore.  Key initiatives include studies on vulnerable tribal groups, support for women researchers, and research projects for undergraduate and postgraduate students.  These initiatives aim to promote inclusivity and address critical social issues.
title: Funding hiked, social science research to get major push

description: A 20-year-old woman in Shamli, Uttar Pradesh, has been arrested for the murder of her father. Initially thought to be a natural death, a postmortem revealed that Satyawan Singh had been strangled. Police investigations revealed inconsistencies in the daughter's account, leading to her confession.
title: UP woman arrested for killing father to foil his bid to sell family land

description: Infosys founder NR Narayana Murthy called for India to reclaim its historical leadership in science and innovation. He argued that invasions and colonization stifled Indian science for centuries, hindering critical thinking and innovation among youth.  Murthy believes that reviving STEM fields is crucial for solving the nation's problems.
title: Invaders & colonisers ruined our science for 1,ooo yrs: Infosys founder

description: A police constable in Agra was arrested for demanding a dowry of Rs 30 lakh from his bride's family on their wedding day. The bride bravely refused to marry him, leading to his arrest and subsequent release on bail. The incident highlights the persistent issue of dowry demands in India, even among those tasked with upholding the law.
title: Cop demands Rs 30 lakh dowry, bride walks out of wedding

description: Anurag Thakur, Former Union Minister, has accused the JMM-Congress-RJD government in Jharkhand of promoting "love jihad" and "land jihad," leading to demographic shifts. He alleged that the government prioritizes appeasement politics over tribal rights and public welfare. Thakur criticized the government's failure to fulfill promises regarding employment, benefits, and tribal welfare, citing corruption and unfulfilled promises as evidence of misgovernance.
title: JMM-Congress’s ‘jihad welfare’ altering J’khand demography: Anurag Thakur
HC upholds priority in jobs for blind over low-vision candidates

description: The Karnataka government has formed a special investigation team (SIT) to probe alleged financial irregularities during the previous BJP government's handling of Covid-19 funds. The SIT will build upon a report that identified potential irregularities amounting to over Rs 7,000 crore, including inflated procurement costs and underreported deaths.
title: Karnataka cabinet OKs SIT probe into ‘BJP-era Covid scam’

description: The Delhi High Court upheld the arrest of Inder Pal Singh Gaba, accused of participating in the March Khalistani protests at the Indian High Commission in London. Gaba was apprehended under UAPA charges for his alleged involvement in the protests where the Indian flag was desecrated.
title: High court rejects man’s plea against his arrest over UK mission stir

description: An Indo-Canadian man, Rajinder Kumar, has been arrested by Canadian Police in connection with the murder of Khalistan supporter, Rabinder Singh Malhi, in Ontario. While police are yet to ascertain the motive, pro-Khalistan groups like Sikhs For Justice (SFJ) allege the involvement of "Hindutva elements" and demand the arrest of a Hindu priest for inciting violence.
title: Man arrested in Canada for killing Khalistan supporter

description: A right-wing group, claiming permission from officials (which was later denied by the administration), demolished a structure inside a Dehradun school calling it an illegal religious structure. The group streamed the act live. While the school is yet to file a complaint, the incident raises concerns about the security of the institution.
title: Mob razes ‘mazaar’ at elite school at Doon in Dehradun

description: Ghulam Ahmed Mir, Congress Jharkhand in-charge, pledged subsidized cooking gas cylinders at a rally, sparking accusations of appeasement politics from the BJP.  PM Modi criticized the promise as a tactic to secure votes, while Congress retorted that BJP is resorting to religious polarization out of desperation.
title: Congress neta's ‘cheaper LPG for infiltrators’ offer sparks row

description: In a surprising move, U.S. President-elect Donald Trump has tapped environmental activist Robert F. Kennedy Jr. to head the Department of Health and Human Services. Kennedy, known for his controversial stance on vaccines, has outlined his health priorities, including tackling chronic diseases and reforming the FDA.
title: Trump picks Robert F Kennedy Jr as secretary of health and human services

description: A landslide in Uttarakhand's Bageshwar district has created a 2,000-meter-long lake, raising concerns about potential downstream devastation.  A multi-departmental team, including geologists and engineers, will assess the lake's stability and the risk of flooding.
title: TOI impact: 2km-lake formed on Shambhu river to be probed by experts

description: The Patna High Court overturned a demotion order of a police inspector. The court observed that the state's prohibition law increased liquor smuggling in Bihar. The law was enacted to improve living standards and public health. The court noted that the law disproportionately affected the poor. The court found the law led to new tactics for smuggling contraband items.
title: Patna high court says liquor law has ended up on wrong side of history
Give invoice to customers: CCPA to Ola

description: Maharashtra Deputy CM Devendra Fadnavis clarified that businessman Gautam Adani was not present at the 2019 BJP-NCP meeting, contrary to Ajit Pawar's claims. Fadnavis asserted that Sharad Pawar, who was present, later betrayed their agreement on government formation. He also indicated the possibility of imposing President's Rule was discussed, with Sharad Pawar tasked to write to the Governor.
title: Adani wasn't part of 2019 talks but Pawar was, and he betrayed us: Fadnavis

description: Khurshid Ahmad, a key suspect in the October 13th communal violence in Maharajganj, Uttar Pradesh, has been apprehended after fleeing to Nepal.  Ahmad allegedly instigated the clash that led to the death of Ram Gopal Mishra and subsequent riots. Police are pursuing three more individuals connected to the violence.
title: Key conspirator in Bahraich immersion clashes held

description: A pregnant woman, her relatives, and a doctor narrowly escaped disaster in Nashik when the ambulance transporting them exploded. The driver, noticing smoke, evacuated everyone moments before the vehicle became engulfed in flames. An investigation has been ordered into the incident, which is suspected to have involved an exploding oxygen cylinder.
title: Narrow escape for pregnant woman as ambulance explodes in Maharashtra

description: Indian Prime Minister Narendra Modi is set to receive Dominica's highest civilian award, the Dominica Award of Honour. The award recognizes Modi's contributions to Dominica during the COVID-19 pandemic, particularly the supply of 70,000 AstraZeneca vaccine doses in 2021.
title: Dominica to honour PM for aid during pandemic

description: A parliamentary committee, revisiting a long-standing debate, is set to discuss the inclusion of "salary" in determining the "creamy layer" for OBC reservation in UPSC exams.  MPs argue that including "salary" contradicts a 1993 order, while the government justifies its stance based on the lack of "equivalence of posts" between PSU and government jobs.
title: Panel to discuss again whether to factor in 'salary' to determine 'creamy layer'

description: Boeing, the aerospace giant, is laying off 10% of its global workforce, approximately 17,000 employees, in a bid to cut costs and streamline operations. CEO Kelly Ortberg attributed the layoffs to financial challenges and the need to enhance competitiveness.
title: Boeing starts layoff for 17k employees; Here's what CEO Kelly Ortberg said

description: A Dalit colony in Madhya Pradesh's Gohta village was attacked by a mob following polling, resulting in four houses being set ablaze and a statue of B.R. Ambedkar vandalized. While locals reported the incident to police, authorities claimed no formal complaint was lodged and downplayed the event as common election-related tension.
title: Dalit houses torched, Ambedkar statue desecrated in MP

description: During election rallies in Maharashtra, Rahul Gandhi accused PM Modi of never reading the Indian Constitution and criticized the BJP's focus on the color of his copy of the document. Gandhi alleged Modi's involvement in the MVA government's downfall, claiming it benefited industrialist Gautam Adani's bid for Mumbai's Dharavi redevelopment project.
title: Why was Adani present at 2019 BJP-NCP meet, asks Rahul Gandhi

description: The Congress party has filed a complaint with the Election Commission against Prime Minister Narendra Modi and Home Minister Amit Shah, alleging that they made divisive and false statements during election rallies in Maharashtra and Jharkhand. The Congress is seeking an immediate ban on campaigning by both leaders.
title: Congress seeks EC action against PM, Shah for ‘poll code violations’

description: Viacom18 and Star India have merged to create India's largest media and entertainment company, valued at over Rs 70,000 crore. The joint venture, backed by Reliance Industries and Disney, will offer a vast library of content across television and digital platforms, including popular channels like Star, Colors, JioCinema, and Hotstar.
title: Reliance Industries, Viacom18 and Disney complete merger

description: The Enforcement Directorate (ED) conducted searches at 20 locations linked to Santiago Martin, a significant political donor known as the 'lottery king,' and his associates. The searches, spanning across multiple states, are part of an ongoing investigation into alleged money laundering related to the illegal distribution and sale of lotteries.
title: ED mounts searches on 20 premises tied to top poll bond buyer

description: Sharad Pawar confirmed a 2019 meeting at Gautam Adani's residence. Amit Shah and Ajit Pawar were present for power-sharing discussions between BJP and NCP. Ajit Pawar stated the meeting involved talks of BJP dropping cases against NCP leaders in exchange for joining forces. Sharad Pawar expressed reservations, leading to the collapse of the short-lived government.
title: Adani hosted 2019 talks but he wasn’t part of it: Sharad Pawar

description: A 14-year-old girl in Kolkata was allegedly drugged and raped by a married neighbor after she rejected his advances. The accused, Pradip Gharami, shared a fake wedding photo of the survivor on social media. The girl attempted suicide and is currently hospitalized. Gharami was arrested and charged under the POCSO Act.
title: 14-year-old drugged, raped by neighbour in West Bengal, 1 held

description: The Indian Supreme Court of India rejected a petition to outlaw WhatsApp due to privacy and security concerns. The petitioner, a software engineer, claimed the messaging app violates the IT Rules and fundamental rights, citing a vulnerability that could compromise communication security. The court found no grounds to entertain the plea.
title: Ban on WhatsApp in India: Here's what Supreme Court said

description: Taylor Swift's Eras Tour continues in Toronto.  Fans wonder if Travis Kelce will attend her concerts. Kelce's NFL commitments with the Kansas City Chiefs might make it difficult. The Chiefs play against the Buffalo Bills on Sunday. Toronto is a short distance from Buffalo.  Kelce's schedule is packed. Fans await to see if Kelce will appear in Toronto.
title: Kelce’s NFL schedule leaves fans guessing about Swift’s Toronto tour

description: The National Investigation Agency (NIA) attached property belonging to Adil Manzoor Langoo, a key suspect in the February killing of two migrant workers in Srinagar.  Langoo, linked to the Lashkar-e-Taiba offshoot The Resistance Front (TRF), was arrested with two others. The NIA alleges the killings were part of a larger conspiracy to spread terror, orchestrated by their Pakistan-based handler.
title: NIA attaches property of terrorist arrested who killed migrants in Kashmir

description: A government school teacher in Chhattisgarh, Rajkumar Ogre, is facing charges for allegedly making derogatory comments about Hindu deities and physically assaulting students who responded by chanting "Jai Shri Ram." Ogre allegedly questioned the educational qualifications of gods and goddesses, prompting the students' religious chants.
title: Teacher faces FIR for thrashing students over ‘Jai shri Ram’ slogan

description: Donna Kelce, mother of NFL star Travis Kelce, addressed rumors about Taylor Swift joining the Kelce family for Thanksgiving. During a "Today" show interview, she shared her holiday plans revolve around football, given Travis’ game schedule. Donna hinted that Swift, busy with her Eras Tour, likely won’t attend, though the couple’s relationship continues to capture public attention.
title: “Will Taylor Swift spend Thanksgiving with the Kelce family? Donna Kelce responds”
How WFH engineer’s password error led to chaos at UK airports

description: Maharashtra Deputy Chief Minister Ajit Pawar claimed that the entire Nationalist Congress Party (NCP), under Sharad Pawar's leadership, was prepared to join the BJP-Shiv Sena government in 2022. He stated that all NCP MLAs, including those currently with Sharad Pawar, had signed a letter supporting the decision.
title: 'Undivided NCP wanted to join Mahayuti govt in 2022': Ajit Pawar

description: The final supermoon of 2024, the Beaver Moon, will grace the night sky on November 16th, appearing larger and brighter as it reaches its closest point to Earth.  This celestial event coincides with beavers preparing for winter and the onset of colder weather.  The Pleiades star cluster will also be visible near the moon, creating a stunning visual spectacle.
title: Last Supermoon of 2024 visible in India on Nov 16: 10 tips to take photos

description: A bomb explosion in northwestern Pakistan's Khyber Pakhtunkhwa province killed at least five people and injured many others.  The blast occurred in the Tappi Dawar area of North Waziristan district. In a separate incident, a suicide bomber blew himself up near a police van in the province's Charsadda district, but no casualties were reported.
title: Blast in Pakistan's Khyber Pakhtunkhwa kills 5, several injured

description: Pakistan has denied any behind-the-scenes talks with India regarding the Champions Trophy.  The Foreign Office spokesperson stated that sports should not be politicized and the PCB is in discussions with the ICC regarding tournament arrangements and team participation, including India's stance on not traveling to Pakistan for the next year's tournament.
title: CT: Pakistan rules out back channel diplomacy with India
'Stop Hasina from making speeches': B'desh govt to India

description: Israel anticipates the new Trump administration will take a tough stance against Iran, potentially paving the way for peace agreements with Arab nations. Energy Minister Eli Cohen expressed optimism that Trump's return could lead to a resolution in Lebanon, pushing Hezbollah away from the border, while emphasizing Israel's right to military action if necessary.
title: Israel expects Trump administration to take hard line on Iran

description: Donald Trump, having secured a Republican majority in the House, is facing pushback from within his own party over his controversial cabinet picks. His nominations of Tulsi Gabbard, Matt Gaetz, and Pete Hegseth for key positions have raised eyebrows, with Gaetz's appointment particularly contentious due to allegations of sexual misconduct.
title: Trump opens the Gaetz of hell after winning trifecta

description: Donald Trump's 2024 campaign promise to dismantle the US Department of Education has ignited debate about the future of American education.  Trump and his supporters advocate for state-controlled education, aligning with their belief in localized oversight.  However, critics argue that abolishing the department could jeopardize funding for disadvantaged students and create inconsistencies in educational standards across states.
title: Decimation of US edu department in Trump 2.0: How real is the threat?

description: Guru Nanak Jayanti is a highly auspicious time for people to come together, share food, and spread kindness. The gurdwaras are beautifully lit at night with lights, candles, and diyas, and vibrant fireworks light up the sky. In the year 2024, Guru Nanak Jayanti will be celebrated on 15th November 2024. To make this occasion even more special, we have curated a beautifully heartwarming list of top 50 Gurpurab wishes, messages, quotes, and images to share with your family and friends.
title: Happy Guru Nanak Jayanti: Top 50 Gurpurab Wishes, Messages, and Images to share

description: President-elect Donald Trump nominated former Democratic Congresswoman Tulsi Gabbard as Director of National Intelligence. Gabbard, who previously faced criticism for her stance on Russia, will lead the US Intelligence Community. The nomination sparked controversy, with some expressing concerns about her qualifications and alleged ties to foreign leaders.
title: Trump names Hindu-American Tulsi Gabbard as US Intel Czar

description: ​Tulsi Gabbard's mother Carol Porter Gabbard was raised in a multicultural household and became interested in Hinduism. All her children have Hindu names -- Bhakti, Jai, Aryan, Tulsi and Vrindavan. Tulsi also follows Hinduism. Old Videos of Tulsi chanting Hare Krishna are viral after she became the first Hindu to head US spy agencies.
title: When Tulsi Gabbard clarified her nationality: 'I am not of Indian origin'

description: Bangladesh's Attorney General proposed significant changes to the Constitution during a High Court hearing. He seeks to remove 'secularism' and 'socialism' as state principles and repeal the amendment criminalizing unconstitutional regime change. He argues that this provision, punishable by death, stifles democratic change and disrespects the recent mass protests that ousted the previous government.
title: B'desh mulls removing 'secularism', 'socialism' from constitution
Will Trump's DOGE be all bark and no bite?

description: Jaya Bachchan's surprise appearance in 'Dil Ka Darwaza Khol Na Darling' has fans buzzing, while Nayanthara gets candid about her love story with Vignesh Shivan.  Meanwhile, Jacqueline Fernandez denies knowledge of gifts from an alleged conman, Anushka Sharma celebrates Children's Day with a special gesture, and Mukesh Khanna questions Tiger Shroff's suitability for the role of Shaktimaan.
title: Fans amazed by Jaya Bachchan in 'Dil Ka Darwaza Khol Na Darling'

description: Google's research head, Yossi Matias, emphasizes the enduring importance of basic coding skills, comparing them to fundamental math. While acknowledging AI's growing role in generating code, Matias highlights the creation of new opportunities and the need for human oversight. He cites AI's impact on healthcare and remains optimistic about the future of coding professions.
title: Why Google's research chief wants everyone to learn coding

description: Taylor Swift and Travis Kelce's romance has been making headlines, not just for their public displays of affection, but also for the extravagant gifts Taylor has showered upon Travis. From designer clothes and luxurious vacations to a Ferrari and a private racetrack experience, Taylor spares no expense when it comes to spoiling her boyfriend.
title: Number of expensive gifts Taylor Swift has given to Travis Kelce

description: An AI-generated video depicting a lighthearted friendship between President Biden and former President Trump has gone viral, garnering millions of views. The video, contrasting with their real-life political rivalry, imagines them enjoying leisure activities together, offering a whimsical escape from the realities of their political roles.
title: Trump, Biden meet at White House: AI video that imagines duo as BFFs goes viral

description: Mahesh Khichi of the Aam Aadmi Party (AAP) was elected as Delhi's first Dalit Mayor, defeating BJP's Kishan Lal by three votes.  Congress abstained from voting. Khichi's term will only last five months due to previous election postponements.
title: AAP's Mahesh Khinchi elected Delhi's new mayor, defeats BJP's Kishan Lal by 3 votes

description: The European Commission has slapped Meta with a hefty €797.72 million fine for allegedly giving Facebook Marketplace an unfair advantage. Regulators claim Meta forced the service on users and leveraged data from advertisers to stifle competition. Meta denies any wrongdoing, arguing that users aren't forced to use Marketplace and that its success stems from meeting consumer demand.
title: EU fines Meta €800 million for 'abusive' practices

description: The University Grants Commission (UGC) has announced plans to allow students to accelerate or decelerate their undergraduate degrees.
title: UGC to allow students to complete degrees in two and half years

description: Many users in India are using weak passwords, according to a new report. The report found that '123456' is the most common password in India. Many of these passwords can be cracked in seconds. Using a combination of uppercase and lowercase letters, numbers, and symbols to create a strong password is recommended.
title: Internet users in India, 20 passwords you should stop using right now

description: During a practice session in Perth, Indian batter Sarfaraz Khan sustained an injury to his right elbow after being struck by a ball. The severity of the injury remains unclear. Sarfaraz's early departure from the session is a concern for the Indian team, given his recent impressive form and potential role in the upcoming first Test against Australia.
title: Sarfaraz walks off after painful elbow hit during net session

description: Arshad Khan, the "Chaiwala" who rose to fame in 2016, secured a Rs 10 million investment on Pakistan's Shark Tank for his tea brand, Chaiwala & Co. Khan aims to expand his brand that offers a traditional Pakistani tea experience with outlets already established in Pakistan and London.
title: Pakistani 'Chaiwala' who became a national sensation makes headlines again

description: Delhi NCR will be under GRAP 3 restrictions starting tomorrow at 8 am due to severe air quality. Construction, demolition, and non-essential mining will be halted. Restrictions on interstate buses and a shift to virtual learning for primary schools are also included.
title: Delhi pollution: GRAP 3 curbs to be imposed as residents choke

description: Mohammed Shami offered a beacon of hope for the upcoming Australia tour, snaring four wickets in his return to red-ball cricket after a year-long injury hiatus. His performance in the Ranji Trophy match is being closely monitored by the national selectors and medical team, with a potential second Test inclusion contingent on his recovery and fitness.
title: Shami to be green lit for Border-Gavaskar Trophy if...

description: Prime Minister Narendra Modi, during a Maharashtra rally, accused Congress of plotting to reinstate Article 370 and create a separate Constitution for Kashmir. He criticized Congress for opposing the BJP's efforts to integrate Kashmir and for allegedly attempting to divide Scheduled Castes, Scheduled Tribes, and Other Backward Classes.
title: Maha poll fight between 'patriots' and 'Aurangzeb admirers': PM Modi

description: India is seeking the extradition of Khalistani terrorist Arshdeep Singh, known as Arsh Dalla, from Canada following his arrest after a shooting incident in Milton, Ontario. Dalla, a proclaimed offender in India with over 50 criminal cases against him, is wanted for various charges including murder, terrorism, and terror financing.
title: 'Will seek extradition': India on arrest of Khalistani terrorist Arsh Dalla in Canada

description: A new Facebook scam is targeting unemployed men in India, promising them large sums of money and property if they impregnate women who post in specific groups. These groups often feature videos of women making these offers, with some even promising upfront payments. However, once the men send money, the scammers disappear.
title: 'Anyone who makes me pregnant in 3 months gets ...': Pregnancy job scams on FB

description: Lahore, Pakistan, is grappling with hazardous smog, recording a pollution index of 1165. Hospitals are overwhelmed with respiratory illness cases, exceeding 15,000 in a day.  The severe air pollution, attributed to industrial emissions and other factors, has prompted school closures, outdoor activity bans, and emergency measures by authorities.
title: Lahore reports over 15,000 respiratory cases in one day due to toxic haze

description: Boeing is issuing layoff notices this week as part of its plan to cut 17,000 jobs, or 10% of its workforce. The layoffs come as the company works to restart production of its 737 MAX aircraft following a recent strike and ongoing safety concerns. Boeing secured $24 billion in financing to stabilize its finances amid the turmoil.
title: Boeing to cut 17,000 jobs, reduce global workforce by 10%

description: In the third T20I against South Africa, Tilak Varma smashed a century after being promoted to number three, leading India to a series lead.  Team management encouraged an aggressive approach, urging players to 'play freely' regardless of wickets lost, a strategy that paid off with Varma's match-winning performance in Centurion.
title: 'Bindaas khelna...': Tilak Varma reveals management's bold message
After Ajit Pawar, 2 BJP leaders reject 'batenge toh katenge' slogan

description: Indian cricket captain Rohit Sharma is training hard in Mumbai for the upcoming Border-Gavaskar Trophy series against Australia.  He is focusing on fitness and skills at Mumbai Cricket Association and Reliance Corporate Park facilities.  Rohit will decide on his travel plans later.  Other Indian players have already arrived in Australia.  The series begins on November 22 in Perth.
title: Watch: Rohit continues to train in Mumbai ahead of BGT

description: Consumer advocacy group Which? has filed a £3 billion lawsuit against Apple, alleging the tech giant inflated iCloud fees and unfairly locked in 40 million UK customers. The group claims Apple's practices limited competition and resulted in overcharged subscriptions, potentially making millions eligible for compensation.
title: Apple faces $3.78 billion lawsuit in UK; here's why

description: Jason Kelce will not be going shirtless at the upcoming Chiefs vs. Bills game. Kelce, now an analyst, will be watching the game from a comfortable spot. He previously went shirtless in Buffalo during a playoff game. Kelce discussed his plans on his podcast, New Heights, with his brother, Travis Kelce.
title: Jason Kelce guarantees he won’t go shirtless during Chiefs’ game against Bills

description: Congress leader Ghulam Ahmed Mir sparked controversy by promising subsidized cooking gas cylinders to "everyone, including infiltrators" if the INDIA bloc wins the election. The BJP condemned the statement, accusing Congress of resorting to religious appeasement, while highlighting its own anti-infiltration campaign in the state.
title: J'khand polls: Cong vows LPG cylinders for 'infiltrators'; BJP slams 'toxic politics'

description: Australian cricketer Glenn Maxwell on Thursday achieved a major milestone. He became the third Australian batsman to score 10,000 runs in men's T20 cricket. He achieved this feat during the first T20I against Pakistan. Maxwell joins David Warner and Aaron Finch in this exclusive club. He is known for his aggressive batting style.
title: Maxwell third Australian to achieve this big feat in Men's T20s
'Never played victim card': Kharge's son on Yogi's 'Razakars' charge

description: Virat Kohli is gearing up for the Border-Gavaskar Trophy in Australia, drawing significant attention from fans in Perth. The upcoming series holds immense importance for Kohli, who faces pressure to solidify his place in the Indian Test team amidst a potential transition phase.
title: Watch: Fans climb trees to catch glimpse of Virat Kohli

description: The Uttar Pradesh Public Service Commission announced that the 2024 PCS Preliminary Exam will be held on a single day. This decision follows recent government changes mandating single-day exams for those with over 500,000 applicants.  Additionally, a committee has been formed to address the logistics of the RO/ARO exam, with an official notification expected soon.
title: After big protest, UPPSC prelims exam 2024 to be held in single day

description: In a surprising turn of events, "Yeh Rishta Kya Kehlata Hai" has clinched the top spot in the TRP ratings, dethroning the long-reigning champion "Anupamaa." The intense pregnancy drama has captivated viewers, leaving them eager for the next episode.
title: Yeh Rishta Kya Kehlata Hai dethrones Anupamaa from the top slot

description: Rajasthan's Mahipal Lomror has smashed a triple century against Uttarakhand in the Ranji Trophy, captivating cricket enthusiasts. His unbeaten 300, achieved with a blend of power and precision, has propelled Rajasthan towards a commanding total. This timely performance showcases Lomror's potential ahead of the 2025 IPL mega auction, signaling his value as a dependable middle-order batsman and handy bowler.
title: Lomror smashes triple century to send reminder to IPL franchises

description: The Central Selection Board of Constable Recruitment (CSBC) has released the Bihar Police Constable results. Candidates can visit the official website to check their results. Those shortlisted will move on to the next phase, the Physical Efficiency Test (PET). The written exam was conducted for 21,391 Constable positions across various Bihar Police divisions. Check the direct link to download the CSBC Bihar Police Constable result 2024.
title: CSBC Bihar Police constable result out: Check here
Haryana: 8 vehicle pile-up on NH9 due to dense fog

description: A man accused of cow slaughter in Meerut, Uttar Pradesh, was injured during a confrontation with police.  While attempting to escape custody, the accused, Amir, allegedly grabbed an officer's pistol and fired. Police returned fire, injuring Amir in the leg. He is currently hospitalized.  A case has been registered against Amir under the IPC and animal cruelty laws.
title: UP: Man accused of cow slaughter injured in police encounter

description: Tensions flared in Bhensi village, Uttar Pradesh, as a Dalit funeral became a flashpoint for alleged caste discrimination. The village head and three others are accused of obstructing the funeral procession of Baburam, who died on November 9th.
title: Village head among four booked for obstructing Dalit's funeral in UP's Khatoli

description: Delhi's air quality dipped to 'severe' with an AQI of 428, prompting the government to enforce stricter pollution control measures under GRAP Stage 2. Environment Minister Gopal Rai attributed the deteriorating air quality to calm winds and lower temperatures, highlighting contributions from both local sources and the National Capital Region.
title: Delhi air pollution: Govt directs strict implementation of GRAP II measures
Key faces in Trump’s Cabinet: Who has been picked so far?

description: Delhi Police arrested SK Masud Alam, a resident of West Bengal, in connection with the Rs 2,000 crore cyberattack on WazirX. Alam allegedly created a fake account that was used to breach the crypto exchange.
title: Police arrests man for WazirX hack: Telegram, fake account & more used

description: Kashyap Bakle and Snehal Kauthankar of Goa etched their names in Ranji Trophy history with an unbeaten 606-run partnership, the highest ever in the tournament's 90 years. Their monumental effort, both scoring triple centuries, propelled Goa to a commanding 727/2 declared against Arunachal Pradesh on Day 2, surpassing the previous record of 594 runs.
title: Goa batters forge highest-ever stand in Ranji's 90-year-old history

description: India's wholesale price inflation accelerated to a four-month high of 2.36% in October, driven by surging food prices, particularly vegetables. While fuel and power costs declined, food inflation soared to 11.59%, impacting potatoes and onions significantly. This surge follows a similar trend in retail inflation, posing potential challenges for the Reserve Bank of India's monetary policy stance.
title: WPI inflation rises to 4-month high as food prices surge

description: Three-year-old chess prodigy Anish Sarkar, the youngest-rated player in history, met his idol, Magnus Carlsen, who offered encouragement and advice. Carlsen, impressed by Anish's abilities, emphasised the importance of enjoying the game over focusing on ratings and titles. Mentored by GM Dibyendu Barua, Anish's exceptional talent has propelled him to achieve remarkable milestones at a young age.
title: Magnus Carlsen meets 3-year-old chess prodigy Anish Sarkar: 'Amazing to see his level'

description: During a rally in Maharashtra, Rahul Gandhi accused Prime Minister Modi of disregarding the Indian Constitution, comparing it to a blank book.
